Title: Reducible representations of CAR and CCR with possible applications to
  field quantization
Authors: Marek Czachor
Comments: Contribution to "New ideas in quantization", XXI Workshop on
  Geometric Methods in Physics, Bialowieza 2002, proceedings to be published in
  J. Nonlin. Math. Phys., jnmp.cls style package included, typos in vacuum
  states corrected
\\
  Reducible representations of CAR and CCR are applied to second quantization
of Dirac and Maxwell fields. The resulting field operators are indeed operators
and not operator-valued distributions. Examples show that the formalism may
lead to a finite quantum field theory.
